cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a convolutional neural network model for gender prediction using English Twitter text as input. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper leverages the trained models to predict gender labels from an HPV vaccine related corpus and identifies gender difference in public perceptions regarding HPV vaccine. 
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper deals with analyzing public perceptions and attitudes towards a health issue using social media data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper uses deep learning techniques for gender prediction.
